main event: A possible meteor observation near Harrisburg, Pennsylvania on August 23, 1955.
interesting points: The object was small, changing colors, and moving at high speed.
The object wobbled along its path from north to south.
The object disappeared in the city lights, and then disappeared instantly a second time.
The observation lasted approximately 16 seconds each time.
The report includes surface weather data and radar readings, but no photograph.
sighted object: small object changing colors and disappearing at high speed
